    "recap_headline": "Tulane University",
    "recap_text": "NEW ORLEANS \u2013\nThe Tulane baseball team (11-11) climbed back to .500 and made it a two straight wins in 2-0 shutout of visiting Northwestern State (13-8) on Wednesday, March 18, on Greer Field at Turchin Stadium.\nJude Abbadessa\n(1-1) earned the victory with four shutout innings with four strikeouts and two hits allowed.\nJ.D. Rodriguez\nstarted and went thre first three innings with three strikeouts and two hits allowed.\nTom Vincent\nthrew 0.2 of an inning with a hit and walk surrendered plus a strikeout.\nJulius Ejike-Charles\nwent 0.1 inning with a walk allowed.\nLuisPablo Navarro\nearned his first save of the season with a pair of strikeouts to preserve the victory in the ninth.\nJohnny Elliott\nled the offense with two hits.\nKaikea Harrison\nhad a hit and an RBI.\nMatthias Haas\ndrove in the other run with an RBI ground out.\nJason Wachs\ntotaled a hit and a walk.\nJames Agabedis\npicked up a hit, a walk and a run scored.\nTanner Chun\nand\nTrent Liolios\neach also walked.\nJacob LeBlanc (2-2) was tagged with the loss for Northwestern State after allowing two runs in the seventh inning.\nThe Green Wave scored both of their runs in the bottom of the seventh inning on a Haas ground out and an RBI single from Harrison.\nNext, Tulane opens conference play and welcomes in Memphis (5-14) for a three-game set from March 20-22 on Greer Field at Turchin Stadium. The game times are 6:30 p.m., 6:30 p.m. and 1 p.m.\nNotables\nJason Wachs\nextended his on-base streak to 48 games from the end of last season and the first 22 games this year with a hit and a walk against Northwestern State\u2026The 48 games is a career high\u2026The win was the team's second straight\u2026Tulane improved the team's all-time record to 21-4 against Northwestern State\u2026The 10 strikeouts recorded by the Tulane pitching staff was the 11th time the program has reached double figures in strikeouts this season\u2026Over the last five games, Tulane's relief pitchers have thrown 35.1 innings with just six runs allowed while striking out 38\u2026\nLuisPablo Navarro\nis the third different Tulane player to record a save this season following\nSam Larson\n(1) and\nTom Vincent\n(2)\u2026The bunt single by\nJames Agabedis\nwas his second hit of the season\u2026The shutout was the first for Tulane since blanking Memphis last season (5/10/25) by a 3-0 margin\u2026Tulane is now 2-0 on Wednesdays this season.\nTICKETS\nTickets for the baseball season and the upcoming football and volleyball campaigns can be purchased by calling 504-861-WAVE (9283), logging on to TulaneTix.com or visiting the ticket office at the James W. Wilson Jr. Center.\nGREEN WAVE CLUB\nGiving to the\u00a0Green\u00a0Wave\u00a0Club\u00a0provides Tulane Athletics with the resources student\u2011athletes need to excel in competition and in the classroom. Your support directly improves the lives of current and future\u00a0Green\u00a0Wave\u00a0student\u2011athletes and enhances Tulane's competitiveness in intercollegiate athletics. Make a gift today by calling (504) 865\u20115356, emailing\ngreen\nwaveclub@tulane.edu\n, or visiting\nGreenWaveClub.com\n.\n---TulaneGreenWave.com---"
